# Content & Ship Data Architecture

Read `docs/Ship_Content_Data_Architecture_Spec.md` before making any changes.

## Core Design Decisions
- Every ship, weapon, and module is a **self-contained folder** under `/content/`
- The **folder name is the item's ID** — no separate ID field in JSON
- One `Ship.tscn` for all ships — configured at spawn time from data, no per-class scenes
- `ContentRegistry.gd` scans `/content/` on startup and indexes everything
- `PlayerState.gd` is the single source of truth for the active player ship
- `ShipFactory.spawn_ship(id, pos)` is the only correct way to instantiate ships

## Directory Layout
```
/content/
    /ships/<id>/        ship.json + model.glb + icon.png
    /weapons/<id>/      weapon.json + model.glb + icon.png
    /modules/<id>/      module.json + icon.png
/data/
    damage_types.json   (global config — NOT content)
    ai_profiles.json    (global config — NOT content)
```

## Rule of Thumb
"If it's something the player can see, equip, or interact with" → `/content/`
"If it's a system configuration table" → `/data/`

## ContentRegistry API
```gdscript
ContentRegistry.get_ship("fighter_light")     # → ship data dict
ContentRegistry.get_weapon("autocannon_light") # → weapon data dict
ContentRegistry.get_module("shield_standard")  # → module data dict
ContentRegistry.get_asset_path(data, "model")  # → "res://content/ships/fighter_light/model.glb"
```

## PlayerState API
```gdscript
PlayerState.set_active_ship(ship)             # emits player_ship_changed signal
PlayerState.get_active_ship() -> Node
```

## PerformanceMonitor Metrics
- `ContentRegistry.load` — wrap the full startup scan in `begin()`/`end()`

## Watch Out For
- Never hardcode a ship class scene path — always go through `ShipFactory`
- `default_loadout` in `ship.json` maps slot/hardpoint IDs to content IDs (folder names)
- Module stat application is deferred post-MVP — MVP ships use hull stats directly
- `damage_types.json` stays in `/data/` — it is a lookup table, not content
- `player_ship_changed` signal is defined in `GameEventBus.gd` and emitted by `PlayerState`
